commit.message:
Switch to CHANGELOG.md for changelogs

Add just for development commands (release process should be much easier now).

Test Python 3.12-dev

Start testing Python 3.12.

Update some of the action versions.

Add assertion to test_fixedoffset_eq and bump test dependencies

Noticed that test_fixedoffset_eq was missing an actual assertion while bumping dependencies (it was flagged by linting).

Bump certifi from 2022.9.24 to 2022.12.7

Bumps [certifi](https://github.com/certifi/python-certifi) from 2022.9.24 to 2022.12.7.
- [Release notes](https://github.com/certifi/python-certifi/releases)
- [Commits](https://github.com/certifi/python-certifi/compare/2022.09.24...2022.12.07)

---
updated-dependencies:
- dependency-name: certifi
  dependency-type: indirect
...

Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>
Freshen up the README and docs

Drop Python 3.6 support

Python 3.6 is end of life.
raise ParseError if we get an exception on is_iso8601()

Add an `__all__` to `__init.py__`

Addresses https://github.com/micktwomey/pyiso8601/issues/17

Add `docs/example.py` with a mypy check to catch similar issues.

Run `pre-commit autoupate`

Run `poetry update`
Remove branch filter from pull requests
